Part 1 Q1:
CPU: Preforms calculations and manages data
GPU: Renders Graphics
RAM: Temporarily stores data that the CPU needs
Motherboard: Connects all the parts together and makes communication between the other parts.
Power Supply: Provides power to the PC
Harddisk: Stores the information and data
Cooling: Keeps the parts cool when they overheat
Case: houses all the parts and have ports that plug into the motherboard

Q2:
Screwdriver and an anti-static strap.
Grounding is important because it absorbs the static energy that may harm a human.